Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, low total CO₂, significant proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with abnormal urine appearance and color. These findings suggest impaired renal function, possible metabolic acidosis, and likely nephrotic-range proteinuria. The presence of glucose and ketones in urine with low HbA1c is unusual and may indicate acute metabolic disturbance. Further nephrological and metabolic evaluation is recommended.
